{"name":"Spellbooks","permission":{"default":0,"hsFJxrWN4M5Ezw3L":3},"type":"feature","data":{"description":"","req":"","source":"cfeature","category":"Wizard","benefit":"You have a selection of spellbooks containing a wide variety of spells, which you can consult to prepare a spell selection appropriate to the situation. \n\nYour main spellbook is created during character creation, and it contains all of the Arcane powers that you know. Spellbooks are physical items: a blank spellbook normally costs 25 gp, but the first spellbook you make during character creation is free.\n\nYou may also create secondary spellbooks which contain a different selection of Arcane powers. When creating a secondary spellbook, pick a number of Arcane powers equal to the number you already know (and with the same number of lesser and greater powers). You then inscribe these powers into the secondary spellbook. You may have a number of secondary spellbooks equal to your Intelligence modifier at any time. Creating a spellbook requires a long rest.\n\nYou may only use powers from your main spellbook, but during a short rest, you may study any of the secondary spellbooks you have with you to make it your main spellbook. Your previous main spellbook then becomes a secondary spellbook.\n\nYou cannot use another wizard’s spellbook unless you spend a long rest studying the spells it contains. This allows you to use it as one of your secondary spellbooks, and it is subject to the same restrictions on the number and type of powers it can contain (if it contains more spells than you could normally use, you must select a subset of them).\n\nWhen you learn a new Arcane power, it is added to your main spellbook, and you may also add one power to each of your secondary spellbooks. \n\nIf you retrain an Arcane power to another Arcane power, it changes the power in your main spellbook, and you may also change one power in each of your secondary spellbooks. \n \nIf you lose an Arcane power by retraining, the power is removed from your main spellbook, and you must also remove one power from each of your secondary spellbooks. \n\nEach of your spellbooks must contain the same types of powers: that means the same number of lesser powers and the same number of greater powers. If you have one or more Arcane powers from a feat or other special source, then all of your spellbooks must have powers from that source—for instance, if you have the collector of cantrips feat that gives you three Cantrip powers, then each of your spellbooks must have three Cantrip powers.\n\nIf your main spellbook is ever lost or destroyed, you remember the Arcane powers that were in it, and you can still use these powers until you switch to a secondary spellbook. You can also scribe the spells you remember into a new spellbook.","notes":"","sources":{"rfeature":{"label":"Racial Feature","value":"rfeature"},"cfeature":{"label":"Class Feature","value":"cfeature"},"ifeature":{"label":"Item Feature","value":"ifeature"},"feat":{"label":"Feat","value":"feat"},"prof":{"label":"Proficiency","value":"prof"},"other":{"label":"Other","value":"other"}}},"flags":[],"img":"icons/svg/book.svg","effects":[],"_id":"AvbnZT9rlu5zGjZM"}
