{"name":"Nimbus of Power","permission":{"default":0,"hsFJxrWN4M5Ezw3L":3},"type":"feature","data":{"description":"","req":"","source":"cfeature","category":"Sorcerer","benefit":"As a minor action, you can surround yourself with a nimbus of arcane energy which lashes out at your foes, granting you several benefits:\n~\tWhenever a creature you have challenged makes an attack roll which suffers disfavor due to your challenge, while within 5 squares of you, it takes 1d8 damage. A creature may only take this damage once per round.\n~\tWhen you use an Arcane ranged or area attack power, you do not provoke opportune strikes from targets of the power. When you use an Arcane area burst power, you may choose to exclude your space from the power’s area.\n~\tYou gain a +2 power bonus to AC while wearing cloth or no armor.\n~\tYou gain 1 armor resistance while wearing cloth or no armor.\n~\tAny weapon you wield counts as a magical weapon.\n~\tYou shed dim light in a 5-square radius.\nYour nimbus lasts until the end of the encounter, until you deactivate it as a minor action, or until you are stunned or incapacitated.","notes":"","sources":{"rfeature":{"label":"Racial Feature","value":"rfeature"},"cfeature":{"label":"Class Feature","value":"cfeature"},"ifeature":{"label":"Item Property","value":"ifeature"},"feat":{"label":"Feat","value":"feat"},"prof":{"label":"Proficiency","value":"prof"},"other":{"label":"Other","value":"other"}}},"flags":[],"img":"icons/svg/book.svg","effects":[],"_id":"jqyjAuE36nEavMTB"}
