{"name":"Gadgets","permission":{"default":0,"hsFJxrWN4M5Ezw3L":3},"type":"feature","data":{"description":"","req":"","source":"cfeature","category":"Artificer","benefit":"You can provide allies with simple magical devices that duplicate your spells. During a short rest, you may create up to <CHA> gadgets. Each gadget contains a copy of one of your Arcane attack or utility powers, and may be given to other creatures. Only powers which require a main, move, or minor action may be stored in gadgets.\nAnother creature carrying one of your gadgets may activate it during their turn as a minor action. This creature can then use the power contained in the gadget as part of that minor action. The power functions exactly like it would if you were using it yourself—it has the same attack and damage bonuses, and benefits from all of your feats and other qualities—but the creature that activated the gadget is the one using the power. A creature can only activate one gadget per round, and only one of your gadgets can be activated per round—if one of your allies tries to activate a second of your gadgets, it has no effect.\nA gadget containing a lesser power can be used any number of times, but a gadget containing a greater power can only be used once. When you create a gadget containing a greater power, you must sacrifice the greater power use at the time of creation.","notes":"","sources":{"rfeature":{"label":"Racial Feature","value":"rfeature"},"cfeature":{"label":"Class Feature","value":"cfeature"},"ifeature":{"label":"Item Property","value":"ifeature"},"feat":{"label":"Feat","value":"feat"},"prof":{"label":"Proficiency","value":"prof"},"other":{"label":"Other","value":"other"}}},"flags":[],"img":"icons/svg/book.svg","effects":[],"_id":"knqMCEHYFJRVNsai"}
